==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hebraize
<hw>He"bra*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to
speak Hebrew: cf. F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧bra⟦ium⟧ser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
convert into the Hebrew idiom; to make Hebrew or Hebraistic.</def>
<rj><au>J. R. Smith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hebraize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hebraize
<hw>He"bra*ize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Hebraized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hebraizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To speak Hebrew, or to conform
to the Hebrew idiom, or to Hebrew customs.</def>⟦br⟧
